This is a known breaking change. In .NET 10, Android enforces **edge-to-edge** display by default, which makes `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` (and its MAUI wrapper) no longer work. You need to react to **IME window-insets** instead.

### Quick fix — handle insets in `MainActivity.cs`

```csharp
// Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs
using Android.OS;
using AndroidX.Core.View;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Let the app draw behind system bars / keyboard
        WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window!, false);

        var content = FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(content, new ImeInsetsListener());
    }

    private class ImeInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var ime = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var systemBars = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.SystemBars());

            // Push content up by whichever is taller: keyboard or nav bar
            v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, Math.Max(ime.Bottom, systemBars.Bottom));
            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

### What this does

| Piece | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(…, false)` | Opts into edge-to-edge; your layout extends behind the keyboard area |
| `WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime()` | Gives you the **keyboard height** in pixels |
| `SetPadding(…, bottom)` | Pushes your content (including the input bar) above the keyboard |

### iOS

iOS already adjusts for the keyboard automatically in most MAUI layouts. If you still see overlap, wrap your chat page content in a `ScrollView` — MAUI's built-in `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (on since .NET 8) will handle the rest. To toggle it explicitly:

```csharp
// MauiProgram.cs  (only if needed)
Microsoft.Maui.Platform.KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Disconnect();   // disable
Microsoft.Maui.Platform.KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Connect();      // re-enable
```

### Layout tip for chat screens

Use a `Grid` with two rows — one `*` (messages list) and one `Auto` (input bar) — so the input bar naturally sits at the bottom and rides up with the padding change:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" />
    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message…" HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

The insets listener above will add bottom padding to the root view, pushing this entire grid up above the keyboard.
